message.content:
An eel is a long and slender fish with a snakelike body that lacks scales.
It has a slimy and smooth skin that is mostly brown or gray in color.
Its body is elongated and can measure up to several feet in length.
Eels have a single, continuous fin that runs along the entire length of their body.
They have a pointed head with small eyes and a wide mouth filled with sharp teeth.
Eels are found in freshwater and saltwater environments all around the world.
They are often used as a delicacy in various cuisines and are also kept as pets.
